# anyapp — Project Conventions

## Platform
- This app is **iOS + SwiftUI only**. Do not add macOS, watchOS, UIKit views, or cross-platform abstractions unless explicitly requested.

## Swift & SwiftUI
- Use the **latest Swift grammar** and modern SwiftUI APIs.
- Prefer SwiftData for persistence (existing pattern in `anyapp/Item.swift`).
- Match existing project structure: app target lives under `anyapp/`.

## Git workflow
- **One branch per function/feature** — do not mix unrelated changes on the same branch.
- **Commit as you work** on each branch; do not leave large uncommitted chunks at the end.
- Use descriptive branch names (e.g. `cursor/recording-ui-3cf7` for agent work).

## App context
- **Plus button** (toolbar in `ContentView`) creates a new `Item`.
- **Item detail view** (currently inline `NavigationLink` destination in `ContentView`) is where features like recording belong.
- Planned direction: recording in item detail as a notebook for thoughts (not yet implemented).

## Key files
- [`anyapp/ContentView.swift`](anyapp/ContentView.swift) — list, plus button, item detail
- [`anyapp/Item.swift`](anyapp/Item.swift) — SwiftData model
- [`anyapp/anyappApp.swift`](anyapp/anyappApp.swift) — app entry + model container
